How To Fix Canon Printer Not Responding Error?

Enter Printer Model


You may have some mistakes with the Canon Printer. “canon mx922 printer not responding” is a regular mistake with all the faults. This mistake can be seen for many reasons, such as Outdated drivers, weakened network links, USB issues, and more. You must take the troubleshooting steps listed below to correct this mistake. These are the fundamental techniques, helping you successfully overcome the mistake

Reset your link to your network

Testing the internet connection is the most simple troubleshooting phase to repair the “canon printer won’t print” mistake. If a cable links the printer to the network, then test that the cable is correctly attached to it or not. Make sure that the printer is correctly wired to the router in the event of a wireless connection. Then, both the printer and router unplug the power cord. After 5 minutes wait, attach the cable again and push the power button.

The restart of the network link and the printer will help you repair the bug. If the mistake continues, you may attempt to take the following other troubleshooting steps.

Run Printer Troubleshooter

The Windows devices have an embedded troubleshooter to repair the canon mx490 not responding error. Follow the procedure below to operate the troubleshooter.

  • First, from the bottom-left corner, you have to press the icon “Start.”
  • And type in the search bar “Troubleshooting.”
  • Choose the “Troubleshooting” option from the search outcome.
  • Click the “Printer” option in the following browser.
  • This extends the option further. Click the “Run the Troubleshooter” now.
  • The problem solver is now starting to detect the problem. Wait till the issue is found by the troubleshooter.
  • If you notice the error in the troubleshooter, the repair methods must be implemented as per the error. Click the option “Apply this fix” in the dialogue which appears and follow the instructions on-screen.
  • Finally, restart the system and verify whether or not the error has been corrected.

Update the driver of your printer

If you use a false or obsolete Canon Printer driver, you can get this mistake. You must update your driver frequently in this situation. If you don’t have much time and stamina to upgrade it each time, the Driver Quick program will automatically attempt to update the software.

Driver Simple is a program that checks the machine instantly and looks for a perfect driver. All the jobs will be completed alone. Your driver, the upgrade, etc., mustn’t fear.

Respect the procedure listed below for using this program.

  • Next, the Driver Configuration file must be downloaded from the official website.
  • Afterward, the program must be mounted. Double-click the configuration file for download. Then allow the app to run and make your system adjustments by pressing “Yes.” Pick the Installation Wizard language. Additionally. Tap the button “Install Now” next.
  • Click on the “Update” tab on the left side of the wizard in the Driver Simple program.
  • You will begin to check for the updates available. You can get a list of alerts until the search has been completed.
  • To install each upgrade, press the “Update” button.

The update will be installed successfully. Try to use the Cannon printer to verify whether or not errors exist.

Disable protection software for third parties

Canon normally displays the error of not responding, so try removing the security software of third parties. The principal cause for this mistake lies in applications like McAfee, AVG, etc, along with dedicated firewalls. You prevent the program from running on your computer and this leads to a failure. Then you attempt to deactivate the firewall to fix the bug. For the following:

Windows:

  • Click the Start Menu then go to the Control Panel and then Programs and then Programs and Features.
  • This will open your device’s list of installed applications.
  • Pick and right-click the third-party protection program.
  • Tap the option “Uninstall.” This launches the process of uninstallation.

Mac:

  • Tap the Program Finder button.
  • The “Applications” option on the left-hand side would appear in the next pane.
  • Search the security service framework for a third party.
  • Pick the program from the top-left corner of the screen and select the “File” button.
  • Pick “Move to Trash” from the options list to uninstall the submission successfully.

Service Reboot Printer Spooler

Canon Printer Spooler is a service designed to handle printer and driver work and correspondence. If the printer spooler doesn’t work, you will get an error that doesn’t respond. Follow the procedure below to correct this error by resetting the unit.

  • Press the “Window” and “R” keys together.
  • The “Run” dialogue box will be opened.
  • Enter “services. MSC” and click on “Ok” in the empty field in the Run box.
  • Now find the Print Spooler option and click on it.
  • Then, from the left-hand side of the screen, press the “Restart” button.

The Canon Printer Not responding Error is corrected successfully.
